article.description: Chris Wray had 21 points and 10 rebounds and his dunk with a second left in overtime lifted Mount Saint Mary's over George Mason 78-76 on Friday night.
article.headline: Wray's OT dunk lifts Mount St Mary's over George Mason 78-76
article.linkText: Wray's OT dunk lifts Mount St Mary's over George Mason 78-76
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- Chris Wray had 21 points and 10 rebounds and his dunk with a second left in overtime lifted Mount Saint Mary's over George Mason 78-76 on Friday night. George Mason's Justin Kier hit two free throws to tie it at 76 with 29 seconds left in overtime before Elijah Long stole the ball from him later and Mount Saint Mary's called a timeout. Wray got the dunk off the inbounds and a steal as time expired. Wray's double-double were career highs, and the Mountaineers (1-3) outrebounded the Patriots (1-2) by 15. Miles Wilson scored a career-high 12 points on 5-of-10 shooting off the bench and Long and Junior Robinson each added 11. Mount Saint Mary's led 38-37 at halftime, but George Mason's Otis Livingston II hit a 3-pointer with seven seconds left to tie it at 70 at the end of regulation. Jalen Jenkins scored 23 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Marquis Moore scored 19 with 13 rebounds for George Mason.
